A tragic plane crash in Greece claimed the lives of all 121 passengers and crew.
Angry relatives confronted airline officials over past decompression issues.
Experts speculated on a possible technical fault leading to the crash.
Witnesses described a chaotic scene with blackened bodies and scattered debris.
The F-16s intercepted the doomed flight, but the pilots were unresponsive.
The crash site was secured as rescue workers recovered black boxes for investigation.
European officials expressed condolences and emphasized the need for improved air safety standards.
The cause of the crash remained unclear, but terrorism was ruled out.
